detail.title: Bring the active set down to 100
detail.description:
The current active set is 125 validators. While it is good to engage more people, looking at the delegated distribution, it doesn't seem to bring more decentralisation to the network. As a matter of fact the highest 100 validators in Voting Power currently hold over 99.6% of the overall bonded tokens. Having 25 extra validators with less than 0.35% combined does not add decentralisation. Instead it adds 25 more signatures which brings traffic overhead, cpu, ram and storage on every produced block. More signatures means more database entries. 
 This overhead makes more cost to everyone while negatively impacting the performance of the Desmos chain and negatively impacting the environment for no added value  
  This proposal aims to improve the performance of desmos and reduce the costs, By doing so desmos will make it easier for a wider range of validators to participate in the network, which also promotes decentralization. 
 @kais_kat Katarina | Nois Network

detail.title: Desmos v4 upgrade
detail.description:
This proposal aims at upgrading the chain software to version v4. Particularly, the new chain software version will be [v4.7.0](https://github.com/desmos-labs/desmos/releases/tag/v4.7.0) containing a lot of new features, improvements and bug fixes. Among many, we find:

 2. The proper support to signing authz transactions using a Ledger device 
 3. The upgrade to cosmos-sdk v0.45.11 and ibc-go v3.4.0 
 4. ...and many others 

 If this proposal passes, the upgrade will be scheduled to happen at height 6,421,610 which is expected to be proposed around Thursday 15th December at 15:00 UTC.

detail.title: Min deposit param change
detail.description:
Considering that: 
 1. one scam and one spam proposals ([#16](https://explorer.desmos.network/proposals/16) and [#17](https://explorer.desmos.network/proposals/17) respectively) have been submitted in the past week; and 
 2. the DSM price currently allows to spam the chain with fake proposals very cheaply 

 we have decided to propose the community to increase the min amount of DSM that should be deposited for a governance proposal from 500 DSM to 2000 DSM (~100$ considering a DSM price of 0.05$). This should make it less likely for bad actors to create scam or spam proposals in the future, preserving the real meaning of on-chain governance.

detail.title: Delete This Scam Chain
detail.description:
# Validators Unduly Influenced.

We proposed a desmos community fund, had 4 applications for people to join the team, and were at 99% yes vote. Mystically, Cosmostation changed their vote from [yes](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/35FE4C9F5761760DD01FBD43EEF494E1B2D6834BDA105A4335D1BD5BCF7F3842) to [no](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/6DD468A07436AB022E16FE98826A31DE0DE0B12589AE6EAF3201AF9ABB4D6D37), SkyNet changed their vote from [yes](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/B1BA5DE55AABAC83B91F632F4709CD3847DF11C7D9FA45FF01714E22C98932A1) to [no](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/659C9471350E1683A542E582E0DFBB8CDB12D15C9DE1BB574CAAA294E1F4F2EF), Stakin changed from [yes](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/7DB3052EA5CB243DEE5D15F143611A1740ACCF7D3C1080ED68F221D9BCE3408D) to [no](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/B21F6A270E91BE5CDB0D7FCE36F01F3856D94D7C25A93D1ABED083D2BF559263), c29r3 changed [yes](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/9A0CCDBADB69998F1771B9340ED36E33CADCE7B0D1E8C7FCD72959CA5526C38C) to [no](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/64C07746257DC3C5C45CE84A0157B2540FC8716A603C6EDB86D2AFF9B3FF970D), Active Nodes changed [yes](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/A68A6FC56A445C1E7F48C8AA06DAD36E30A81A21EA452191985FAB62D421264C) to [no](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/txs/BA9E6EFBDAFFE8D6F95A3E6A3D746756B354D69F67058EB5894B777F95D10052), and others did too. Seems pretty weird that everyone agreed and then suddenly didn’t huh? Almost like the team pressured them into stopping the community from saving a dead chain.

# This Chain Is Fucking Dead

 October 20, the chain did less than 2k in daily volume, the day of submission of the community fund proposal, the chain did less than 3k. The fact that this project has been around for over a year with NOTHING to show for it is pathetic. Who builds on this chain? Who even votes?? Only XXX wallets voted on this prop compared to [XXX on Cosmos](), [XXX on Akash](), [XXX on Osmosis](), etc! Only [XXX non-validators voted no](). Has there ever been a more clear VC controlled scam-coin? We tried to help by saving the community, but got crushed by the validators. Wanna know something else funny? We didn’t get a SINGLE email from a validator asking us any questions, nor from scam VC team, nobody. Everyone just mystically votes no and continues to be satisfied with no products, no volume, and no one giving a fuck. How about this? How about we leave being a meme to the meme coins and fucking stop validating these shit chains that crush community and hold on to control for dear life as they do fucking nothing. Desmos pile of shit.

# Why Community Pool Spend?

 Vote yes to dump on these motherfuckers to show them how it feels.

detail.title: Create Desmos Community Funding Program
detail.description:
# It's time to ramp up innovation on Desmos.

The first Desmos proposal passed [13 months ago](https://www.mintscan.io/desmos/proposals/1) and there is still no working product on Desmos. Many other chains have had successful community funds to drive development and progress. Right now the community pool is sitting at over 11 million desmos and trading volume (Oct. 19) is sitting at only $2,500/day. This chain is dying and is in desperate need of community engagement! We propose the creation of the Desmos Community Funding Program which can submit funding applications to desmoscommunityfund@telnet.8shield.net for review. Anybody is welcome to join the committee and we will publish quarterly reports of any funded projects. We will immediately reach out to DesignDAO to help us make a professional website and report all expenditures. Half of the funds will be staked for longevity of the program, and funding will be in pools of 100,000 dsm, allowing us to fund 10 projects. We are requesting 1 million dsm. Bear in mind that since volume is essentially non-existent, this will likely not equate to $50,000 in total funding, but will be less. We need to take action to save desmos.

detail.title: Change of the Inflation Rate
detail.description:
### Overview

This proposal aims to change the inflation rate of DSM between `6%` to `15%` (Currently at `65.54%`) and Goal Bonded to `67%`.

### Proposal of Changes

We are proposing the following changes:

* Inflation Max: from `80%` to `15%`
* Inflation Min: from `40%` to `6%`
* Goal Bonded: from `90%` to `67%`

If you agree on this, please vote __YES__.

If you do not agree on this, please vote __NO__.

If you do not understand what this is, please vote __ABSTAIN__.

If you think this is a spam, please vote __NO WITH VETO__.

detail.description: Set the minimum commission to 5%. This will help ensure network stability. It also ensures that validators earn enough to support secure and stable validation. We must create a healthier network. If this proposal is accepted, it will mean that the blockchain needs to be updated so that the fee of all validators can be changed automatically.

detail.title: Desmos v2.3.1 upgrade
detail.description:
This proposal aims at upgrading the chain software to version v2.3.1. 
 This version updates Cosmos to v0.44.4 and fixes the bug that we have identified with vesting accounts and is currently preventing some people from performing any transactions. 

 You can read more about such changes [here](https://github.com/desmos-labs/desmos/releases). Please note that in order to make sure your node can upgrade safely, you will need to have Cosmovisor [**v1.0.0**](https://github.com/cosmos/cosmos-sdk/releases/tag/cosmovisor%2Fv1.0.0) installed. This mean **you will need to upgrade** if you are currently using Cosmovisor v0.1.0. If you need help installing it please join our [Discord chat](https://discord.desmos.network). 

 By voting YES to this proposal you will signal that you are ready for the upgrade. If this proposal passes, the upgrade will be scheduled to happen at height 1,347,305 which will be around Monday 6th December at 13:30 UTC.

detail.title: Desmos v2.3.0 upgrade
detail.description:
This proposal aims at upgrading the chain software to version v2.3.0. 
 This version brings a lot of changes to Desmos, including (but not limited to): 
 1. Upgrading to [Cosmos v0.44.3](https://github.com/cosmos/cosmos-sdk/releases) 
 2. Updating the code to be compatible with [Band v2.3.1](https://github.com/bandprotocol/chain/releases) 
 3. Allowing to avoid specifying a DTag when updating your profile 
 4. And many more improvements to the profiles module. 

 You can read more about such changes [here](https://github.com/desmos-labs/desmos/releases). Please note that in order to make sure your node can upgrade safely, you will need to have Cosmovisor [**v0.1.0**](https://github.com/cosmos/cosmos-sdk/releases/tag/cosmovisor%2Fv0.1.0) (**NOT** v1.0.0) installed. If you need help installing it please join our [Discord chat](https://discord.desmos.network). 

 By voting YES to this proposal you will signal that you are ready for the upgrade. If this proposal passes, the upgrade will be scheduled to happen at height 1.149.680 which will be around Monday 22nd November at 13:00 UTC.

detail.title: Turn on DSM Inflation
detail.description:
This governance proposal is to turn on the inflation described in the [Desmos Project Plan](https://www.desmos.network/files/desmos-project-plan-v0.4.2.pdf).
If this proposal is passed, annual inflation of `DSM` will be between 40% to 80% according to the level of staking ratio.
If you agree on this, please vote `YES`.
If you do not agree on this, please vote `NO`.
If you do not understand what this is, please vote `ABSTAIN`.
If you think this is a spam, please vote `NO WITH VETO`.
